      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KAMARAN (9) worked to find the lead and kept kicking to score last time out at this circuit and distance, giving him three wins and a placing from his last four starts. Drawn to enjoy a cosy run and if he gets the gaps he can take care of this line-up. BUSLIN BRODY (5) led from a similar draw last start and kept going to score in a nice return to form at Bendigo, getting home by 6.5 metres. He can make an impact again. BAR TAB (12) has finished fourth despite breaking in both outings since a Melton win. Has trialled since the latest outing. Has winning claims with manners. ARTIGAS (6) hasn't raced since in breaking in a Victoria Derby heat six months ago but was readied with a trial win and won the only time he attempted this distance. Can open this campaign with a positive effort.",
